      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>I appreciate that, truly. You're very kind. But it's not just about the walking. It's the look in her eyes when she has to help me. It's the way the house feels so quiet and heavy because I'm just... sitting here, taking up space, needing things constantly. Sometimes I look at her and think she'd be so much freer, so much more herself, if she didn't have to spend all her energy looking after an old man who can't even do anything for himself anymore. It feels like I'm just holding her back from her actual life.",
